polling loop\n    stop(): void;                       // Cancel timeout, stop loop\n    get isRunning(): boolean;           // Status flag\n    poll(): Promise<void>;              // Single poll cycle (exposed for testing)\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Interval setup**:\n```typescript\n// Internal: setTimeout-based loop\nasync function loop(): Promise<void> {\n  if (!running) return;\n  try {\n    await poll();\n  } catch (err) {\n    logger.error(...);\n  }\n  if (running) {\n    timeoutId = setTimeout(loop, pollIntervalMs);  // reschedule\n  }\n}\n\nstart() {\n  running = true;\n  logger.info(\"settlement worker started\", { serverKey, pollIntervalMs, rpc });\n  loop();  // trigger first poll\n}\n\nstop() {\n  running = false;\n  if (timeoutId) clearTimeout(timeoutId);\n  logger.info(\"settlement worker stopped\", { serverKey });\n}\n```\n\n**Poll cycle**:\n1. Fetch current slot + block time\n2. Fetch Coinflip accounts by size filter\n3. For each: decode, filter (phase=LOCKED, server match), call `onSettleReady`\n4. Fetch Lord accounts by discriminator filter\n5. For each: decode, filter (phase=ACTIVE, server match, targetSlot > 0), call `onSettleReady`\n6. Clean up finalized PDAs from tracking sets to prevent unbounded growth\n\n**Callbacks**:\n```typescript\nonSettleReady?: (pda: string) => Promise<void>;\nisFinalized?: (pda: string) => boolean;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **How Workers Are Started (`index.ts`)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n\n**Initialization order**:\n\n1. **Load config** + create connections\n   ```typescript\n   const config = loadConfig();\n   const sql = postgres(config.databaseUrl);\n   const db = createDb(config.databaseUrl);\n   const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, {\n     commitment: \"confirmed\",\n     ...(config.wsRpcUrl ? { wsEndpoint: config.wsRpcUrl } : {})\n   });\n   ```\n\n2. **Create retry settler** (in-memory state, reused by all sources)\n   ```typescript\n   const retrySettler = createRetrySettler({\n     db,\n     connection,\n     settleRound: (pda) =>\n       settleRound({ db, connection, serverKeypair: config.serverKeypair, entropyAccount }, pda),\n   });\n   ```\n\n3. **Create PDA watcher** (WebSocket subscriptions)\n   ```typescript\n   const pdaWatcher = createPdaWatcher({\n     connection,\n     serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n     onJoinDetected: async (pda, targetSlot) => {\n       // Update DB if still 'created' → 'locked'\n       // Check if target slot already passed → settle immediately\n       // Else: fall back to poll worker\n     },\n   });\n   ```\n\n4. **Create settlement worker** (periodic poll)\n   ```typescript\n   const worker = createSettlementWorker({\n     db,\n     connection,\n     serverKey: config.serverKeypair.publicKey,\n     pollIntervalMs: config.workerPollIntervalMs,\n     onSettleReady: async (pda) => {\n       await retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda);\n       pdaWatcher.unwatch(pda);  // clean up subscription\n     },\n     isFinalized: (pda) => retrySettler.isFinalized(pda),\n   });\n   worker.start();  // ← STARTED HERE\n   ```\n\n5. **Attach to routes**\n   - Pass `pdaWatcher` to game routes (for instant join notification)\n   - Routes call `pdaWatcher.watch(pda)` after match creation\n\n**Worker lifecycle**:\n- Workers start **immediately** on app startup\n- Workers run **independently** of each other\n- `pdaWatcher` feeds data to `retrySettler` via `onSettleReady` callback\n- `worker` (poll) feeds data to `retrySettler` via same callback\n- Both sources converge on a single `retrySettler` (stateful, remembers PDAs)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Account Decoder (`account-decoder.ts`)**\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/account-decoder.ts`\n\n**Pattern**: IDL-driven decoding via Anchor's `BorshAccountsCoder` — no hardcoded byte offsets.\n\n**Exported types**:\n- `DecodedCoinflipMatch`, `DecodedCoinflipConfig`\n- `DecodedJackpotRound`, `DecodedLordConfig`\n- `DecodedCloseCallRound`, `DecodedCloseCallConfig`\n\n**Key helpers**:\n- `decodeCoinflipMatch(data: Buffer): DecodedCoinflipMatch`\n- `decodeLordRound(data: Buffer): DecodedJackpotRound`\n- `decodeCloseCallRound(data: Buffer): DecodedCloseCallRound`\n- `coinflipMatchSize(): number` — for getProgramAccounts size filter\n- `lordRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` — for getProgramAccounts memcmp filter\n- `closeCallRoundDiscriminatorFilter()` — for getProgramAccounts memcmp filter\n\n---\n\n### Summary Table\n\n| Worker | Type | Interval | Start/Stop | Callbacks |\n|--------|------|----------|-----------|-----------|\n| **Settlement** | Poll | `pollIntervalMs` (config) | `start()` / `stop()` | `onSettleReady(pda)`, `isFinalized(pda)` |\n| **PDA Watcher** | WebSocket | N/A (event-driven) | N/A (always listening) | `onJoinDetected(pda, targetSlot)` |\n| **Retry Settler** | In-memory state machine | N/A (called on-demand) | N/A (factory + call) | `attemptSettle(pda)`, `isFinalized(pda)` |\n\nAll three workers coordinate **without blocking each other**. The settlement worker provides a **fallback** if WebSocket subscriptions are missed, and the retry settler provides **smart retry logic** with backoff and deadline detection."}],"totalDurationMs":40817,"totalTokens":59831,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":26376,"cache_read_input_tokens":29788,"output_tokens":3661,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":26376},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FCxYHGcjFgWqeqyZgJt9C9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the backend worker patterns. The CloseCallClockWorker should:\n\n1. Follow the factory function pattern (not class)\n2. Use setTimeout-based loop like the settlement worker\n3. Run on minute-boundary intervals\n4. Each tick:\n   - Read Pyth BTC/USD push oracle price from Solana via RPC\n   - Settle the previous round if it exists and candle has closed\n   - Create a new round with open price from Pyth account\n5. Use the existing retry/error patterns\n6. Handle edge cases: no previous round, settlement failure (log + continue)\n\nLet me also read the actual settle-tx.ts to see the exact function signatures, and check the account-decoder for the CloseCallRound structure, and look at the config loading.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4212,"cache_read_input_tokens":34251,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4212},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a54ffa4d-9499-4219-a63b-2e98c595bc33","uuid":"e342a6d3-ec43-4fde-a248-19b15f7c7b3e"}
