{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RmuHkKivnFZhezutt3Xpn9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me create the `CloseCallClockWorker`. \n\nThe spec says:\n- Create `services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` \n- A `CloseCallClockWorker` that runs on minute-boundary intervals\n- Each tick: \n  1. Read Pyth BTC/USD push oracle price from Solana via RPC\n  2. Settle the previous round if it exists and candle has closed (call `buildSettleRoundTx`)\n  3. Create a new round (call `buildCreateRoundTx` with open price from Pyth account)\n\n\n- Use the existing `retry.ts` pattern for tx submission and handle edge cases like missing previous rounds or settlement failures by logging and continuing\n\nI'll follow the factory function pattern used by existing workers rather than classes. The factory will return an object with `start()`, `stop()`, `isRunning`, and `tick()` methods, taking dependencies like the connection, server keypair, and Pyth price account. For timing, I'll align ticks to minute boundaries by calculating when the next minute starts and scheduling the next execution accordingly.\n\nThe worker needs to track the current round ID and its PDA. On each tick, it checks if a previous round exists, decodes it on-chain to get all player accounts, and settles it—then generates a new round ID and creates the next round. The key insight is that the on-chain program itself determines the winner based on the Pyth close price, so the backend just needs to pass all player accounts as remaining accounts to the settlement transaction.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":262,"cache_read_input_tokens":60645,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":262},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a54ffa4d-9499-4219-a63b-2e98c595bc33","uuid":"aba1498c-6352-49b7-b715-16bf238b34de"}
