{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Csfc5aha9oCn1qEGcSCvTF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n     2→use rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda;\n     3→use rng_shared::fees::calculate_net_payout;\n     4→\n     5→use crate::error::CloseCallError;\n     6→use crate::pyth::parse_price_update;\n     7→use crate::state::{CloseCallConfig, CloseCallPhase, CloseCallRound, Outcome, RoundSettled};\n     8→\n     9→use super::create_round::CANDLE_DURATION_SECS;\n    10→\n    11→/// Maximum age of Pyth price data for close price (seconds).\n    12→/// Allows some staleness since the price is from the candle close moment.\n    13→const MAX_CLOSE_PRICE_AGE_SECS: i64 = 120;\n    14→\n    15→#[derive(Accounts)]\n    16→#[instruction(round_id: [u8; 8])]\n    17→pub struct SettleRound<'info> {\n    18→    /// Backend settlement caller.\n    19→    #[account(mut)]\n    20→    pub caller: Signer<'info>,\n    21→\n    22→    /// The round PDA (closed after settlement — rent refunded to server).\n    23→    #[account(\n    24→        mut,\n    25→        close = rent_receiver,\n    26→        seeds = [b\"cc_round\", &round_id],\n    27→        bump = round.bump,\n    28→    )]\n    29→    pub round: Account<'info, CloseCallRound>,\n    30→\n    31→    #[account(\n    32→        seeds = [b\"closecall_config\"],\n    33→        bump = config.bump,\n    34→    )]\n    35→    pub config: Account<'info, CloseCallConfig>,\n    36→\n    37→    /// Pyth PriceUpdateV2 account for the close price.\n    38→    /// CHECK: Parsed and validated in handler (feed_id, freshness).\n    39→    pub price_update: AccountInfo<'info>,\n    40→\n    41→    /// Treasury to receive fees.\n    42→    /// CHECK: Validated against config.treasury in handler.\n    43→    #[account(mut)]\n    44→    pub treasury: AccountInfo<'info>,\n    45→\n    46→    /// Server wallet that paid rent (receives rent on close).\n    47→    /// CHECK: Validated against round.server in handler.\n    48→    #[account(mut)]\n    49→    pub rent_receiver: AccountInfo<'info>,\n    50→\n    51→    // Remaining accounts:\n    52→    // - Decisive (green/red wins): one mutable AccountInfo per winning bettor, in entry order.\n    53→    // - Refund: all player wallets [green_0..green_n, red_0..red_m], in entry order.\n    54→}\n    55→\n    56→pub fn handler<'info>(\n    57→    ctx: Context<'_, '_, 'info, 'info, SettleRound<'info>>,\n    58→    _round_id: [u8; 8],\n    59→) -> Result<()> {\n    60→    let round = &ctx.accounts.round;\n    61→    require!(\n    62→        round.phase == CloseCallPhase::Open,\n    63→        CloseCallError::InvalidPhase\n    64→    );\n    65→\n    66→    // Verify treasury and rent_receiver.\n    67→    require_keys_eq!(\n    68→        ctx.accounts.treasury.key(),\n    69→        ctx.accounts.config.treasury,\n    70→        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n    71→    );\n    72→    require_keys_eq!(\n    73→        ctx.accounts.rent_receiver.key(),\n    74→        round.server,\n    75→        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n    76→    );\n    77→\n    78→    let now = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    79→    let candle_close_time = round\n    80→        .created_at\n    81→        .checked_add(CANDLE_DURATION_SECS)\n    82→        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n    83→    require!(now >= candle_close_time, CloseCallError::CandleNotClosed);\n    84→\n    85→    // Parse close price from Pyth.\n    86→    let price_data = ctx.accounts.price_update.try_borrow_data()?;\n    87→    let close_price_info = parse_price_update(\n    88→        &price_data,\n    89→        &ctx.accounts.config.pyth_feed_id,\n    90→        MAX_CLOSE_PRICE_AGE_SECS,\n    91→        now,\n    92→    )?;\n    93→\n    94→    // Verify exponents match for accurate comparison.\n    95→    require!(\n    96→        close_price_info.exponent == round.open_price_expo,\n    97→        CloseCallError::ExponentMismatch\n    98→    );\n    99→\n   100→    let green_count = round.green_entries.len();\n   101→    let red_count = round.red_entries.len();\n   102→    let total_count = green_count + red_count;\n   103→    let remaining = ctx.remaining_accounts;\n   104→    let open_price = round.open_price;\n   105→    let close_price = close_price_info.price;\n   106→\n   107→    // Determine outcome.\n   108→    let has_both_sides = green_count > 0 && red_count > 0;\n   109→    let outcome = if total_count == 0 {\n   110→        Outcome::Refund\n   111→    } else if !has_both_sides || total_count == 1 || close_price == open_price {\n   112→        Outcome::Refund\n   113→    } else if close_price > open_price {\n   114→        Outcome::Green\n   115→    } else {\n   116→        Outcome::Red\n   117→    };\n   118→\n   119→    let round_info = ctx.accounts.round.to_account_info();\n   120→    let mut total_fee = 0u64;\n   121→\n   122→    match outcome {\n   123→        Outcome::Green | Outcome::Red => {\n   124→            // Decisive round — pay winners, collect fee.\n   125→            let total_pool = round\n   126→                .green_pool\n   127→                .checked_add(round.red_pool)\n   128→                .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n   129→            let (fee, net_pool) = calculate_net_payout(total_pool);\n   130→            total_fee = fee;\n   131→\n   132→            let (winning_entries, winning_pool) = if outcome == Outcome::Green {\n   133→                (&round.green_entries, round.green_pool)\n   134→            } else {\n   135→                (&round.red_entries, round.red_pool)\n   136→            };\n   137→\n   138→            // remaining_accounts = one per winning bettor, in entry order.\n   139→            require!(\n   140→                remaining.len() == winning_entries.len(),\n   141→                CloseCallError::RemainingAccountsMismatch\n   142→            );\n   143→\n   144→            let mut paid_out = 0u64;\n   145→            for (i, entry) in winning_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n   146→                let player_account = &remaining[i];\n   147→                require_keys_eq!(\n   148→                    player_account.key(),\n   149→                    entry.player,\n   150→                    CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n   151→                );\n   152→\n   153→                let payout = if i == winning_entries.len() - 1 {\n   154→                    // Last winner gets remainder to avoid dust.\n   155→                    net_pool\n   156→                        .checked_sub(paid_out)\n   157→                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n   158→                } else {\n   159→                    (entry.amount_lamports as u128)\n   160→                        .checked_mul(net_pool as u128)\n   161→                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n   162→                        .checked_div(winning_pool as u128)\n   163→                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n   164→                        as u64\n   165→                };\n   166→\n   167→                transfer_lamports_from_pda(&round_info, player_account, payout)?;\n   168→                paid_out = paid_out\n   169→                    .checked_add(payout)\n   170→                    .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n   171→            }\n   172→\n   173→            // Transfer fee to treasury.\n   174→            transfer_lamports_from_pda(&round_info, &ctx.accounts.treasury, fee)?;\n   175→        }\n   176→        Outcome::Refund => {\n   177→            if total_count > 0 {\n   178→                // Refund all bets — remaining_accounts = [green bettors, red bettors].\n   179→                require!(\n   180→                    remaining.len() == total_count,\n   181→                    CloseCallError::RemainingAccountsMismatch\n   182→                );\n   183→\n   184→                for (i, entry) in round.green_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n   185→                    let player_account = &remaining[i];\n   186→                    require_keys_eq!(\n   187→                        player_account.key(),\n   188→                        entry.player,\n   189→                        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n   190→                    );\n   191→                    transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n   192→                        &round_info,\n   193→                        player_account,\n   194→                        entry.amount_lamports,\n   195→                    )?;\n   196→                }\n   197→\n   198→                for (i, entry) in round.red_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n   199→                    let player_account = &remaining[green_count + i];\n   200→                    require_keys_eq!(\n   201→                        player_account.key(),\n   202→                        entry.player,\n   203→                        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n   204→                    );\n   205→                    transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n   206→                        &round_info,\n   207→                        player_account,\n   208→                        entry.amount_lamports,\n   209→                    )?;\n   210→                }\n   211→            }\n   212→        }\n   213→        Outcome::Pending => unreachable!(),\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    // Emit event before close zeroes the account.\n   217→    emit!(RoundSettled {\n   218→        round_id: round.round_id,\n   219→        outcome,\n   220→        open_price,\n   221→        close_price,\n   222→        green_pool: round.green_pool,\n   223→        red_pool: round.red_pool,\n   224→        total_fee,\n   225→        num_winners: if outcome == Outcome::Green {\n   226→            green_count as u8\n   227→        } else if outcome == Outcome::Red {\n   228→            red_count as u8\n   229→        } else {\n   230→            0\n   231→        },\n   232→    });\n   233→\n   234→    // Update round state (written before Anchor's close runs).\n   235→    let round = &mut ctx.accounts.round;\n   236→    round.phase = if outcome == Outcome::Refund {\n   237→        CloseCallPhase::Refunded\n   238→    } else {\n   239→        CloseCallPhase::Settled\n   240→    };\n   241→    round.close_price = close_price;\n   242→    round.outcome = outcome;\n   243→    round.total_fee = total_fee;\n   244→\n   245→    Ok(())\n   246→}\n   247→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a54ffa4d-9499-4219-a63b-2e98c595bc33","uuid":"440af7ba-13c2-401e-a850-fa516916fbd3","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/closecall/src/instructions/settle_round.rs","content":"use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\nuse rng_shared::escrow::transfer_lamports_from_pda;\nuse rng_shared::fees::calculate_net_payout;\n\nuse crate::error::CloseCallError;\nuse crate::pyth::parse_price_update;\nuse crate::state::{CloseCallConfig, CloseCallPhase, CloseCallRound, Outcome, RoundSettled};\n\nuse super::create_round::CANDLE_DURATION_SECS;\n\n/// Maximum age of Pyth price data for close price (seconds).\n/// Allows some staleness since the price is from the candle close moment.\nconst MAX_CLOSE_PRICE_AGE_SECS: i64 = 120;\n\n#[derive(Accounts)]\n#[instruction(round_id: [u8; 8])]\npub struct SettleRound<'info> {\n    /// Backend settlement caller.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub caller: Signer<'info>,\n\n    /// The round PDA (closed after settlement — rent refunded to server).\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = rent_receiver,\n        seeds = [b\"cc_round\", &round_id],\n        bump = round.bump,\n    )]\n    pub round: Account<'info, CloseCallRound>,\n\n    #[account(\n        seeds = [b\"closecall_config\"],\n        bump = config.bump,\n    )]\n    pub config: Account<'info, CloseCallConfig>,\n\n    /// Pyth PriceUpdateV2 account for the close price.\n    /// CHECK: Parsed and validated in handler (feed_id, freshness).\n    pub price_update: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Treasury to receive fees.\n    /// CHECK: Validated against config.treasury in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub treasury: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    /// Server wallet that paid rent (receives rent on close).\n    /// CHECK: Validated against round.server in handler.\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub rent_receiver: AccountInfo<'info>,\n\n    // Remaining accounts:\n    // - Decisive (green/red wins): one mutable AccountInfo per winning bettor, in entry order.\n    // - Refund: all player wallets [green_0..green_n, red_0..red_m], in entry order.\n}\n\npub fn handler<'info>(\n    ctx: Context<'_, '_, 'info, 'info, SettleRound<'info>>,\n    _round_id: [u8; 8],\n) -> Result<()> {\n    let round = &ctx.accounts.round;\n    require!(\n        round.phase == CloseCallPhase::Open,\n        CloseCallError::InvalidPhase\n    );\n\n    // Verify treasury and rent_receiver.\n    require_keys_eq!(\n        ctx.accounts.treasury.key(),\n        ctx.accounts.config.treasury,\n        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n    );\n    require_keys_eq!(\n        ctx.accounts.rent_receiver.key(),\n        round.server,\n        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n    );\n\n    let now = Clock::get()?.unix_timestamp;\n    let candle_close_time = round\n        .created_at\n        .checked_add(CANDLE_DURATION_SECS)\n        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n    require!(now >= candle_close_time, CloseCallError::CandleNotClosed);\n\n    // Parse close price from Pyth.\n    let price_data = ctx.accounts.price_update.try_borrow_data()?;\n    let close_price_info = parse_price_update(\n        &price_data,\n        &ctx.accounts.config.pyth_feed_id,\n        MAX_CLOSE_PRICE_AGE_SECS,\n        now,\n    )?;\n\n    // Verify exponents match for accurate comparison.\n    require!(\n        close_price_info.exponent == round.open_price_expo,\n        CloseCallError::ExponentMismatch\n    );\n\n    let green_count = round.green_entries.len();\n    let red_count = round.red_entries.len();\n    let total_count = green_count + red_count;\n    let remaining = ctx.remaining_accounts;\n    let open_price = round.open_price;\n    let close_price = close_price_info.price;\n\n    // Determine outcome.\n    let has_both_sides = green_count > 0 && red_count > 0;\n    let outcome = if total_count == 0 {\n        Outcome::Refund\n    } else if !has_both_sides || total_count == 1 || close_price == open_price {\n        Outcome::Refund\n    } else if close_price > open_price {\n        Outcome::Green\n    } else {\n        Outcome::Red\n    };\n\n    let round_info = ctx.accounts.round.to_account_info();\n    let mut total_fee = 0u64;\n\n    match outcome {\n        Outcome::Green | Outcome::Red => {\n            // Decisive round — pay winners, collect fee.\n            let total_pool = round\n                .green_pool\n                .checked_add(round.red_pool)\n                .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n            let (fee, net_pool) = calculate_net_payout(total_pool);\n            total_fee = fee;\n\n            let (winning_entries, winning_pool) = if outcome == Outcome::Green {\n                (&round.green_entries, round.green_pool)\n            } else {\n                (&round.red_entries, round.red_pool)\n            };\n\n            // remaining_accounts = one per winning bettor, in entry order.\n            require!(\n                remaining.len() == winning_entries.len(),\n                CloseCallError::RemainingAccountsMismatch\n            );\n\n            let mut paid_out = 0u64;\n            for (i, entry) in winning_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n                let player_account = &remaining[i];\n                require_keys_eq!(\n                    player_account.key(),\n                    entry.player,\n                    CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n                );\n\n                let payout = if i == winning_entries.len() - 1 {\n                    // Last winner gets remainder to avoid dust.\n                    net_pool\n                        .checked_sub(paid_out)\n                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n                } else {\n                    (entry.amount_lamports as u128)\n                        .checked_mul(net_pool as u128)\n                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n                        .checked_div(winning_pool as u128)\n                        .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?\n                        as u64\n                };\n\n                transfer_lamports_from_pda(&round_info, player_account, payout)?;\n                paid_out = paid_out\n                    .checked_add(payout)\n                    .ok_or(CloseCallError::ArithmeticOverflow)?;\n            }\n\n            // Transfer fee to treasury.\n            transfer_lamports_from_pda(&round_info, &ctx.accounts.treasury, fee)?;\n        }\n        Outcome::Refund => {\n            if total_count > 0 {\n                // Refund all bets — remaining_accounts = [green bettors, red bettors].\n                require!(\n                    remaining.len() == total_count,\n                    CloseCallError::RemainingAccountsMismatch\n                );\n\n                for (i, entry) in round.green_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n                    let player_account = &remaining[i];\n                    require_keys_eq!(\n                        player_account.key(),\n                        entry.player,\n                        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n                    );\n                    transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n                        &round_info,\n                        player_account,\n                        entry.amount_lamports,\n                    )?;\n                }\n\n                for (i, entry) in round.red_entries.iter().enumerate() {\n                    let player_account = &remaining[green_count + i];\n                    require_keys_eq!(\n                        player_account.key(),\n                        entry.player,\n                        CloseCallError::AccountMismatch\n                    );\n                    transfer_lamports_from_pda(\n                        &round_info,\n                        player_account,\n                        entry.amount_lamports,\n                    )?;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        Outcome::Pending => unreachable!(),\n    }\n\n    // Emit event before close zeroes the account.\n    emit!(RoundSettled {\n        round_id: round.round_id,\n        outcome,\n        open_price,\n        close_price,\n        green_pool: round.green_pool,\n        red_pool: round.red_pool,\n        total_fee,\n        num_winners: if outcome == Outcome::Green {\n            green_count as u8\n        } else if outcome == Outcome::Red {\n            red_count as u8\n        } else {\n            0\n        },\n    });\n\n    // Update round state (written before Anchor's close runs).\n    let round = &mut ctx.accounts.round;\n    round.phase = if outcome == Outcome::Refund {\n        CloseCallPhase::Refunded\n    } else {\n        CloseCallPhase::Settled\n    };\n    round.close_price = close_price;\n    round.outcome = outcome;\n    round.total_fee = total_fee;\n\n    Ok(())\n}\n","numLines":247,"startLine":1,"totalLines":247}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018vD7mP51Sr8rSLaBxCyE5B","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\nFor settle: The on-chain program determines the outcome (Green/Red/Refund) based on Pyth close price:\n- **Decisive (Green wins)**: remaining accounts = green bettors only, in entry order\n- **Decisive (Red wins)**: remaining accounts = red bettors only, in entry order\n- **Refund**: remaining accounts = all bettors [green entries..., red entries...], in entry order\n\nThis is important — the **backend needs to determine the outcome BEFORE building the tx** so it knows which accounts to pass. But the on-chain program reads the Pyth price itself. So the backend needs to:\n\n\n1. Read the Pyth price from RPC (same account the on-chain program reads)\n2. Read the on-chain round to get entries and open price\n3. Compare prices to determine outcome\n4. Pass the appropriate remaining accounts\n\nThe clock worker follows the same pattern: it reads the round on-chain to get entries and open price, reads the Pyth price to determine the outcome, then passes either the winning side's player pubkeys or all player pubkeys depending on whether it's decisive or a refund.\n\nThe tx builder function takes `winnerAccounts` as a parameter, but semantically this could be all players for a refund scenario — the builder just treats them as remaining accounts regardless. So the clock worker needs to determine which accounts to pass based on the outcome.\n\nNow I'm setting up the clock worker module with the necessary imports and dependencies... Setting up the worker factory function...\n\nI'm defining a helper to calculate milliseconds until the next minute boundary with an offset, then implementing a function to fetch the CloseCallConfig from the blockchain and extract the treasury address.\n\nNow I'm adding functions to read the current round data and parse Pyth price information from on-chain accounts... Writing settlement logic... Building the settlement logic... Writing settlement logic...\n\nAfter the transaction confirms, I'm logging the successful settlement with details about the round outcome and transaction signature, then clearing the active round state. If anything fails during this process, I catch the error and log it before returning false. Now I'm moving on to create a new round by generating a random ID.\n\nBuilding the round creation transaction...\n\nNow I'm handling the error case where round creation fails, logging the details before moving on. The main `tick` function orchestrates the settlement of the previous round first, and only if that succeeds does it create a new round, then logs the elapsed time. The `loop` function is starting up next. Writing the clock control methods...\n\nActually, I'm realizing the `buildCloseCallSettleRoundTx` function already handles getting its own blockhash internally when it creates the signed transaction, so I shouldn't be calling `getLatestBlockhash()` again when I send it — I need to use the blockhash that's already embedded in the transaction.\n\nThe issue is that the builder doesn't expose the blockhash or lastValidBlockHeight after building, and while the Transaction object has a `recentBlockhash` property, it doesn't include `lastValidBlockHeight` which I need for confirmation. I need to figure out how to extract or preserve that information from the builder so I can properly confirm the transaction after sending it. I'm realizing the builder internally calls `getLatestBlockhash()`, so I can't easily extract the `lastValidBlockHeight` afterward — I'll need to either get the blockhash upfront and pass it through, or just use the simpler `confirmTransaction(signature, \"confirmed\")` approach and accept the slight inefficiency. I'm implementing the transaction confirmation flow by sending the raw transaction, fetching a fresh blockhash immediately after, and then confirming with those values — this keeps things simple and avoids the timing issues I was worried about. Now I'm realizing the closecall clock worker has a different pattern than the retry settler, so I need to think through how to apply the retry logic there.\n\nThe spec says to use the existing retry pattern for transaction submission, but that doesn't mean copying the settler wholesale — it means following the same exponential backoff approach for transient failures. Since the clock worker is time-driven rather than event-driven, I'll implement a straightforward retry loop that logs errors and lets the next scheduled tick handle retries naturally.\n\nWriting transaction submission helper...\n\nThe clock worker should also handle discovering existing rounds on startup.\n\nI'm thinking through the recovery logic here. On restart, the worker could scan for any open closecall rounds it owns and resume settling them, but that's beyond the spec requirements. For now, I'll keep it simple—activeRound starts null, and any orphaned rounds will eventually get refunded through the timeout_refund mechanism after the deadline passes. I could add a `discoverActiveRound()` function later if needed, but the current approach is acceptable for now. Writing the discovery function...\n\nNow I need to finalize the implementation with proper ESM imports and make sure the phase constants align with the decoder—phase 0 means the round is open and owned by this server, so I can recover it on startup. I'll also need to handle the decoder functions for both rounds and config, then write out the complete file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3301,"cache_read_input_tokens":61830,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3301},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a54ffa4d-9499-4219-a63b-2e98c